## CQRS — Command Query Responsibility Segregation

Separate the **write model** (Commands) from the **read model** (Queries).

```
Commands:  CreateOrder, CancelOrder, ShipOrder → write to event store
Queries:   GetOrder, ListOrders, SearchOrders → read from optimized projections
```

This solves the **impedance mismatch**: the data model optimized for writes is rarely optimal for reads.

```java
// Command side — rich domain model
@CommandHandler
public void handle(PlaceOrderCommand cmd) {
    validate(cmd);
    apply(new OrderPlacedEvent(cmd.getOrderId(), cmd.getItems()));
}

// Query side — simple read model
@QueryHandler
public OrderSummary handle(GetOrderQuery query) {
    return orderSummaryRepository.findById(query.getOrderId());
    // reads from a denormalized, query-optimized table
}
```

## Snapshots

To avoid replaying all events on every load, periodically create **snapshots** of aggregate state:

```java
// Every 100 events, save snapshot
if (aggregate.getVersion() % 100 == 0) {
    snapshotStore.save(new Snapshot(aggregate.getId(), 
                                    aggregate.getState(), 
                                    aggregate.getVersion()));
}

// On load: find latest snapshot, then replay only events after it
Snapshot snap = snapshotStore.findLatest(aggregateId);
List<Event> events = eventStore.getEventsAfter(aggregateId, snap.getVersion());
// Replay only recent events on top of snapshot
```
